detaileddescription.para: Get the contact manifold. Do not modify the manifold unless you understand the internals of Box2D.
Enable/disable this contact. This can be used inside the pre-solve contact listener. The contact is only disabled for the current time step (or sub-step in continuous collisions).

briefdescription.para: Get the next contact in the world's contact list.
Get fixture A in this contact.
Get the child primitive index for fixture A.
Get fixture B in this contact.
Get the child primitive index for fixture B.
Evaluate this contact with your own manifold and transforms.
Flag this contact for filtering. Filtering will occur the next time step.

memberdef.argsstring: (b2Fixture *fixtureA, int32 indexA, b2Fixture *fixtureB, int32 indexB, b2BlockAllocator *allocator)

detaileddescription.para: The class manages contact between two shapes. A contact exists for each overlapping AABB in the broad-phase (except if filtered). Therefore a contact object may exist that has no contact points.
